org.openimaj.video.processing.tracking

Interface ObjectTracker<O,I>

  • Type Parameters:
    O - The type of objects that will be tracked
    I - The type of image in which the objects will be tracked
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BasicMBFImageObjectTracker, BasicObjectTracker

    public interface ObjectTracker<O,I>
    An interface for classes that can track objects in video (or image streams).
    Author:
    David Dupplaw (dpd@ecs.soton.ac.uk)

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • initialiseTracking

        List<O> initialiseTracking(Rectangle bounds,
                           I image)
        Initialise the tracking with the given target area in the given image.
        Parameters:
        bounds - The target area to track in the image
        image - The image to initialise the tracking with
        Returns:
        A list of found objects (may be empty if no object found); should not be null.

      • trackObject

        List<O> trackObject(I image)
        Track the object in the image.
        Parameters:
        image - The image to continue tracking the object within.
        Returns:
        The list of objects found in the image
